Is it easy?

297
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:45,960
My mother

298
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:49,840
passed away when I was young.

299
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:51,970
As for my dad,

300
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:54,320
he was never home all year round.

301
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:56,440
In my memory,

302
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:58,280
I was always alone.

303
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,280
A scene like today

304
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:04,570
is something I wouldn't even dare to dream of.

305
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,600
Actually, I'm quite like you.

306
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,960
When I was a kid,

307
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:17,080
I was always alone too.

308
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:18,480
It's just that

309
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:22,000
my parents had an accident

310
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,480
and could never come back.

311
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,080
I was ten that year,

312
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:31,280
like an angry bird.

313
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,040
I hated

314
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:36,760
everyone who pitied and cared for me.

315
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:39,040
I'd rather starve

316
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,880
than eat the food sent by my aunts.

317
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,600
With nothing to eat,

318
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,930
I learned to cook by myself.

319
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,810
I almost burned the house down.

320
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:51,440
And then?

321
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:54,040
Then,

322
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:57,960
it was Grandpa.

323
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:02,000
Grandpa pulled me out of the mire.

324
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:10,880
Are you unhappy?

325
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:12,840
Grandpa,

326
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:15,320
am I just bad at everything?

327
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:19,050
If you want to learn to cook,

328
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,730
why didn't you ask your aunts for help?

329
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:23,890
I don't want to trouble others.

330
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,120
Come, drink some tea.

331
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,860
Keep Grandpa company for a while.

332
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:37,240
Rong,

333
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:38,840
do you know

334
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:41,880
why our village is called Gechen Village?

335
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:48,000
A long, long time ago,

336
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,720
in this village of ours,

337
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:52,440
there was only a family with the surname Ge living here.

338
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:53,680
One year,

339
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:56,480
a family with the surname Chen fled famine and passed by here,

340
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:57,760
