447
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:43,120
The clothes

448
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:45,680
are also his favorite.

449
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:48,770
He divided the little money left in the bankbook,

450
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:51,280
had a meal with the family,

451
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:55,480
and drank the red rice wine brewed by his aunt.

452
00:22:56,800 --> 00:22:59,000
We also took a big group photo together.

453
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:04,880
He repeatedly told us

454
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:06,920
that when he passed away,

455
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:09,560
the house should be decorated with lanterns inside and out,

456
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:11,020
and set off firecrackers.

457
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:13,040
He also said

458
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:15,800
that this day in the future

459
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:17,520
should not be treated as a death anniversary,

460
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:18,720
but as a festival

461
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,400
to celebrate for him.

462
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:24,720
Grandpa is really a free-spirited person.

463
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:31,240
Let Grandpa tell you,

464
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:34,000
a person's life

465
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:36,200
is like climbing a mountain.

466
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:39,320
Going up the mountain first, then coming down.

467
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:42,820
If you don't want to regret when coming down,

468
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,930
you must enjoy yourself to the fullest when going up.

469
00:23:46,040 --> 00:23:48,300
How do you enjoy yourself to the fullest?

470
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:52,000
When you see a flower you like,

471
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:52,720
